    <h1>IN&#xAD;SUR&#xAD;ANCE FOR YOUR RENTED CAR</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200806/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-06"><time>2020-08-06</time></a>
        - <span>VEHICLES PROPERTIES</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Rent­ing a car is a con­ve­nient way for in­di­vid­u­als with busy life­styles to hit the road. When mis­for­tune strikes, hav­ing proper car in­sur­ance is es­sen­tial to en­sure your peace of mind and pro­tect you from fi­nan­cial risk.</p>
    <p>Car in­sur­ance is a con­tract that cov­ers you against ac­ci­dents on the road. For a pre­mium sum, you will be in­sured against the in­curred costs of an ac­ci­dent such as prop­erty, med­i­cal and li­a­bil­ity cov­er­ages.</p>
    <p>Hav­ing valid car in­sur­ance pro­tects you from con­sid­er­able fi­nan­cial risk.</p>
    <p>Be aware of the dif­fer­ent tiers of in­sur­ance and check that your cov­er­age and li­a­bil­i­ties are ex­plained clearly.</p>
    <p>When rent­ing a car, you should look out for the in­sured value of the in­sur­ance cov­er­age. You should also check the ex­cess charges for self col­li­sion.</p>
    <p>NEED TO FI­NANCE YOUR VE­HI­CLE PUR­CHASES? CHECK OUT THINK ONE.</p>


